obo:SYMP_0000858 obo:IAO_0000115 "Hypokinesia is a musculoskeletal system  symptom characterized by the slow or diminished movement of body musculature. It may be associated with basal ganglia diseases; mental disorders; prolonged inactivity due to illness; experimental protocols used to evaluate the physiologic effects of immobility; and other conditions." ;
    ns3:hasOBONamespace "symptoms" .

