<https://w3id.org/ocd#Contamination_Intrusive_Image> a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/ocd#Intrusive_Image> .

<https://w3id.org/ocd#Doubt_Intrusive_Thought> a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:comment "Doubt obsessions can be characterized as persistent and distressing uncertainties or hesitations regarding various aspects of life. These may include doubts about personal actions, decisions, beliefs, or morality." ;
    rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/ocd#Intrusive_Thoughts> .

<https://w3id.org/ocd#Hoarding_Intrusive_Thought> a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:comment "The concept of hoarding can be illuminated by examining hoarding obsessions as described in Y-BOCS. These hoarding thought may encompass the differentiation between one's hobbies and concerns related to objects with monetary or sentimental value." ;
    rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/ocd#Intrusive_Thoughts> .

<https://w3id.org/ocd#Psychological_Treatment> a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:comment "Psychological treatment, also known as psychotherapy or talk therapy, refers to a range of therapeutic interventions designed to help individuals manage and overcome mental health issues, emotional difficulties, and behavioral problems." ;
    rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/ocd#Treatment> .

<https://w3id.org/ocd#Sexual_Intrusive_Thought> a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:comment "The understanding of sexuality can be gleaned by examining it through the lens of sexual obsession described in Y-BOCS. These sexual obsession may encompass forbidden or perverse sexual thoughts, explicit images, or impulsive desires, some of which might involve highly sensitive content related to children or incest. Additionally, this obsession could extend to concerns surrounding homosexuality and issues related to sexual behavior towards others, particularly in an aggressive context. These can become intrusive when accompanied by negative emotions, time-consuming behaviors, and functional impairments." ;
    rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/ocd#Intrusive_Thoughts> .

<https://w3id.org/ocd#Sexual_Intrusive_Urge> a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:comment "An intrusive sexual urge refers to a recurring, distressing sexual urge/impulse that is intrusive and unwanted." ;
    rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/ocd#Intrusive_Urge> .

<https://w3id.org/ocd#Somatic_Intrusive_Thought> a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:comment "The concept of somatic experiences can be illuminated by considering it through the lens of somatic obsession delineated in Y-BOCS. These somatic obsession may revolve around excessive concerns with illness or disease, leading to heightened apprehension regarding one's health. They can also encompass preoccupations with specific body parts or aspects of appearance, a condition known as dysmorphophobia. Additionally, these contents may manifest in various other forms, creating intrusive experiences when linked to negative emotions, time-consuming rituals, and functional impairments." ;
    rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/ocd#Intrusive_Thoughts> .

<https://w3id.org/ocd#Somatic_Intrusive_Urge> a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:comment "An intrusive somatic urge refers to a recurring, distressing somatic urge/impulse that is intrusive and unwanted." ;
    rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/ocd#Intrusive_Urge> .

